//First aid instructions : Heart Attack
Never overlook a person suffering from chest pain. Make the person sit in a slightly reclined angle. Let the person take a rest and try to keep him or her calm. Loosen his or her tighten clothes. Ask the person whether he or she takes any chest pain medicines like nitroglycerin, for recognized heart condition, and assist them in taking it. If a person still experiences pain within 3 minutes of taking nitroglycerin, call for emergency medical assistance. In the case of infant or child is unresponsive and unconscious condition, perform 1 minute of CPR, then call 161. A person suffering from a heart attack should receive medical care within one hour. If a person is in an unconscious condition and unresponsive, call 161 (or your local emergency number), then start CPR. Push hard and fast on the center of the victim\'s chest. 100 â€“ 120 times per minute. Tilt the victims head back and lift the chin to open the airway. Give mouth to mouth rescue breaths.
